Weekend inspiration: Embrace nature in style @killercatmountainhouse, a newly listed Airbnb in Hunter, NY that delivers an unexpected Catskills experience. 

Inside, the Parisian-chic decor is a design lover's dream—while outside, a firepit, hot tub and sauna let outdoor enthusiasts unwind and indulge, all year round.

Features include:
🏠 Four bedroom, three bathroom home sleeping 10 guests;
⛷️ 5 minutes to Hunter Mountain, 15 minutes to Windham Mountain;
🏔️ 900-sq-ft deck with direct Hunter Mountain views;
♨️ Outdoor hot tub, hot-barrel sauna and firepit;
🔥 Living room with fireplace and 16-foot slider for indoor-outdoor enjoyment;
📺 Samsung 55” Frame TV with a wide array of streaming apps;
🕺🏼 Marshall speaker and Crosley record player with vintage record collection;
👩‍🍳 Fully equipped, custom-designed kitchen;
🍽️ Dining space for 8 guests;
🏓 Game room with arcade machines, ping pong and board games;
💻 Designated work station with high-speed internet.

This ultra-luxe retreat offers a unique getaway in the Catskills, whether you plan to explore the area or just check-in and "check out."

Rates begin at $450/night. For availability, check the link in @escape_brooklyn or @killercatmountainhouse bio.

Photos: @dirtandglass

New in EB travel: @modchaletcatskill in East Jewett, NY. ✨ 

Less than 15 minutes to Windham Mountain & Hunter Mountains, this stylish chalet is the perfect getaway spot year-round — but especially during winter for apres-ski vibes by the fire with a drink, or soaking in the hot tub.

Features include:
🏠 Three bedrooms, two bathrooms sleeping up to 10 guests;
🛁 Primary bathroom with jacuzzi soaking tub;
🔥 Sun-drenched living room with large picture windows & Italian pellet stove for cozy nights by the fire;
🍽️ 100 inch white oak dining table seating 10; 
🌲 Large deck with outdoor seating, grill, gas fire pit and hot tub;
⚡️ Electric vehicle charger;
⛷️ Less than 15 minutes to Windham Mountain, or 10 to Hunter Mountain.

This modern getaway books far in advance, but just released some winter dates for all you last minute planners. Rates begin ~$600/night.

See more from our stay in IG stories today. For rates and availability, plus our mini-guide to the area, check the link in bio — or book direct via the link in @modchaletcatskill bio.

New in EB real estate: this airy turnkey, modern cabin 80 miles from NYC in Pond Eddy, NY ✨

The two bedroom, two bathroom new build was completed in autumn and has all the perks you’d expect in a new home (eco-friendly & WiFi equipped appliances, brand new everything, updated systems) and more. Features include:

🏠 Two bedroom, two bathroom cabin with office/loft space, plus finished basement, on .53 acres;
☀️ Plentiful natural light with vaulted ceilings, skylights, large windows & doors throughout;
🌀 Spiral staircase connecting three levels;
🌲 Multiple decks and patios;
👩‍🍳 Brand new kitchen with LG Smart appliances;
🚿 Maya indoor spa with sound, TV, steam, rain shower and jetted tub;
🔥 Hearthstone Heritage Soapstone wood fire stove;
🌿 4-season screened-in porch;
💦 Hear the magical sound of Mill Brook Creek from this stream adjacent location;
🚗 Short drive to Bethel Woods, numerous quaint towns, farmers market and walkable to the Delaware River.

More pics and info, link in bio. Asking $599,000. ‼️ Open House ‼️ Saturday 1/21/23 at 42 Swanerbury Road in Pond Eddy, NY from 10 am to 3 pm.

Listed by Kevin E. Friel of Unique Properties of Lumberland, LLC. For showings or inquiries, email k.friel@allticketsinc.com or text/call (201) 914-2476.

New in EB real estate: the DeBruce Lodge in Livingston Manor, NY. 

Perched high on over five private acres, this timeless post and beam lodge is located within the Catskills Park’s "Forever Wild" forest preserve and is just 110 miles to NYC. Features include:

🏡 Two bedrooms (+ bonus loft) and one bathroom;
🌳 1,080 square foot home on 5.37 aces;
🔥 Cozy stone fireplace, plus a pellet stove for supplemental heat;
🪟 Airy cathedral ceilings and skylights in living room;
🚿 Floor to ceiling slate finished bathroom with a walk-in shower;
🪵 Heavy timber carpentry and a wood-swathed interior;
⚡️Energy efficient, petroleum-free design boasting a minimal carbon footprint;
💰 Established short-term rental;
🌿 Outdoor shower, native flower garden, and fire pit;
🚘 Close proximity to numerous fishing spots, swimming holes and hiking trails – and 10 minutes into the buzzy town of Livingston Manor, NY.

Asking $425k. Listed by Robin Jones, @catskillmountainhouses. More pics and info, link in bio.

‼️Open house this weekend‼️Saturday January 7, from 12-2 pm at 105 Goff Road Livingston Manor NY 12758. For showings, inquiries, or to RSVP for the open house, email robin@catskillmountainhouses.com.

New in EB travel: the @hurleywhirley, a midcentury-modern treasure in Hurleyville, NY ✨

100 miles from NYC, this super-stylish 4-bedroom vacation rental is full of delightful surprises and thoughtful touches. There’s much to explore in this home, like an entire wing of the home hidden behind swinging doors, disguised as a wall. In the living room, floor-to-ceiling window overlooking the woods gives guests the sensation of treehouse living; while an entire wall of mirrors in one of the bedrooms makes for a captivating bedroom experience. Finally, down the stairs into a fully finished basement, a second living room has a cozy wood stove, plus a bar tucked into a nook, giving off speakeasy vibes.

We absolutely adore this midcentury modern getaway. Features include:

🏠 Four bedrooms, three bathrooms sleeping up to 8 guests;
🛋️ Dual living rooms, one with a wall of windows, the other with a cozy wood stove & bar;
👩‍🍳 Fully stocked kitchen, ideal for cooking large group meals;
🍽️ Separate dining spaces include sunny breakfast nook and formal dining table;
🌿 Spacious deck located off living room for meals al fresco;
🔥 Outdoor space with fire pit and additional dining table;
🛍️ Convenient location walkable to Main St. Hurleyville, with restaurants, bars, hiking, and boutique shops. 

In the same spirit of delightful surprises and thoughtful touches, guests also receive a $50 voucher to use during their stay at nearby @hurleyvillegeneralstore to stock up on goods – plus a spread of Italian specialty foods from local gem @lasalumina – awaiting your arrival.

Rates begin ~$400/night; book direct via @hurleywhirley’s link in bio. Use our mini-guide, at @escape_brooklyn link in bio, to plan a stay (with lots of spring and summer availability) including nearby hikes, restaurants, adventures and more.

Photos: @escape_brooklyn

New in EB real estate: in bucolic Lexington NY, this beautifully preserved farmhouse — with a pristine 1840’s red barn — has been renovated by a designer with a modern aesthetic, celebrating the home’s history and the landscape that surrounds it.

Features include:

🏠 Five bedroom, 4.5 bathroom home;
🐎 Pristine post & beam, two-story red barn;
🌳 2724 square foot home on 2.42 acres;
🛏️ Two ensuite bedrooms, one with fireplace;
🌿 Large screened in porch for al fresco meals
🔨 Recently renovated in 2022, including design/reconfiguration but also systems updates;
⛷️ Close proximity to Hunter, Belleayre, and Windham Mountains.

Asking $1.495m. More pics and info, link in bio.Listed by Regina Tortorella @secondhomeguru, Coldwell Banker Village Green Realty. For showings or inquiries email secondhomeguru@gmail.com or call/text (914) 466-0329.

Photos: @alonkoppelphotography

Weekend inspiration: the new @habitasonhudson in Rhinebeck, NY ✨

Set on a property featuring a renovated 18th-century manor, @habitasonhudson is a 20-room countryside retreat and playground for the curious with activities centered around wellness, music, adventure, art & culture, food, and learning. 

It’s the newest “home” by international hospitality group Habitas — known for luxury lodges and unique villa style accommodations in Saudi Arabia, Mexico, Morocco and Namibia. The Hudson Valley location is the first Habitas project in the United States.

Designed as a holistic escape from the city, Habitas-on-Hudson invites people to come together to play, explore and learn among the sights and sounds of nature. Property highlights & programming includes:

🏠 Three unique buildings providing unique experiences for guests, ranging from the liveliness of the main house to immersion in nature;
🍴 Seasonal menu at on-site restaurant & pub, Social, with regular live music performances and artist popups; 
🎨 Forthcoming artist residence program featuring artists from different spaces (music, wellness and audition) for onsite activations;
🌿 Guided hikes to learn about the local flora and fauna;
🔥 Outdoor amenities including s’mores fire pit, tennis court, barrel sauna and cold plunge pool;
🧘‍♀️ Wellness rituals including yoga, holotropic breathwork, and sound healing baths.

All programming is free of charge, included in room rate. So locals and travelers may enjoy, the Social restaurant is open to the public.

Regular room rates begin ~$450/night; but now until March 31, Escape Brooklyn followers will get a special intro rate of ~$350. 💫 Use the link in bio for the embedded discount code link, or use code ESCAPE on the Habitas website.

New in EB real estate: a timeless beauty, Love Farmhouse is nestled on 60 acres of private trails, meadows and forests with an in-ground pool overlooking the overlapping hills of Rock Valley. 

This rural estate is located in the Catskills foothills and just 120 miles from New York City. Features include:

🏡 2,016 square foot four bedroom, three bathroom 1920’s farmhouse;
🌳 60.31 acres with private trails, creek, meadow and forest;
🏊🏼‍♀️ 20'x40' heated in-ground pool;
🌿 Large screened porch for al fresco meals;
🔥 Living room with cozy wood burning stove;
🪵 Ornate, original wood details throughout;
🛋️ Most furnishings and home contents included in sale.

More pics and info, link in bio. Asking $649k. Listed by Robin Jones, @catskillmountainhouses. 

Open House 🏡 Saturday January 21 noon-2pm. For showings or inquiries, or RSVP to open house, email robin@catskillmountainhouses.com.

New in EB real estate: the Hidden Pond Cabin in Fremont Center, NY.

120 miles from NYC, the Hidden Pond Cabin located in the outskirts of Roscoe, NY – home of fly fishing, local breweries, and more. Located on 10+ acres, this secluded location with a pond is an established, Airbnb rental home generating passive income. 

Features include:

🏡 Three bedroom, three bathroom cabin;
🌳 1,950 square foot home on 10.2 acres;
🛏️ Bonus outbuilding with additional bedroom;
🔥 Floor to ceiling fireplace;
🍿 Private movie theater;
✨ Firepit area overlooking private pond;
♨️ Hot tub, sauna and plunge tub.

Asking $1.3m. More pics and info, link in bio. Listed by Gina Sullivan, @ginasullivan247 Cozy Catskill Realty. For inquiries or showings, email cozycatskillrealty@gmail.com or call (845) 866-8226.

New in EB real estate: Blackberry House, dreamed up and created by brilliant minds behind @homestedt. 

This designer-built stunning home with a sauna and deeded lake rights is located in the Catskills foothills, 100 miles from NYC. 

Features include:
🏠 Three bedroom, two bathroom 1,600 square foot home;
🔨 New build by @homestedt design team, completed in 2022;
🌳 5.72 acre property with deeded lake access to Hust Pond;
🔥 Living room with soaring ceilings, oversize windows, and cozy wood-burning stove;
☀️ Expansive sundeck, outdoor shower and sauna;
🛁 Primary en-suite bedroom with walk-in shower and separate soaking tub;
💻 Loft area with lounge and workspace;
✨ All new utilities, appliances, and finishes. 

All contents have been handpicked for the space by designer Anna Åberg of @homestedt and are available for sale, making this a truly turn-key home. Minutes to Jeffersonville, Livingston Manor, and Callicoon — Blackberry House’s location is ideal as a weekend getaway or full-time residence. 

Asking $695k. More pics and info, link in bio. Listed by Robin Jones @catskillmountainhouses. ‼️ Open house ‼️ Saturday January 28 noon-2pm. For showings, inquiries, or to RSVP to the open house, contact robin@catskillmountainhouses.com.

Photos: 1, 5, 10 by @pbcrosby; 2-4, 6-9 by @catskillimage.

Weekend inspiration: the incredibly scenic & unique @bentapplefarm in Londonderry, Vermont – who's getting 2+ feet of snow this week! ✨ (Snow chasers, get on this!) 

At Bent Apple Farm, five distinctly cozy rentals are available over a rolling 80 acre landscape that’s perfect for snowshoeing and cross-country skiing. Lodging options range from tiny cabins to an expansive luxury farmhouse that accommodates big groups. Available as single, double, or entire property rentals, take advantage of the proximity to ski mountains – where it’s forecasted to get 2-3 feet of white, powdery snow this week.

Features at Bent Apple Farm include: 

🎨 Art Studio: cabin with loft & wood burning stove, sleeping 4 guests; 
🏠 Tack Room: a tiny cabin with a wood burning stove, sleeping 2 guests;
🐴 Rustic barn with a wood stove and outdoor shower, sleeping 4 guests; 
🍎 Bent Apple Farmhouse, a luxurious farmhouse sleeping 10 guests; 
🌳 Stunning 80 acre landscape situated between mountains and rolling hills, perfect for cross-country and snowshoeing;
♨️ Hot tub, and sauna for guest use when renting any property;
🧊 Swimming pond that transforms into skating pond during cold months;
 ⛷️ Close proximity (under 15 minutes) to Magic, Bromley, Stratton, Okemo and Killington ski mountains – plus scenic sleigh riding at a farm less than 5 minutes away.

Whether you’re a big group, travel-loving couple, or a solo traveler looking for a unique getaway, Bent Apple Farm has something low-key and totally cozy to offer in one of the most scenic parts of the northeast. 

Rates begin at $120/night with lots of availability this winter. Explore Bent Apple Farm via the link in @escape_brooklyn or @bentapplefarm's bio.

Photos: @dirtandglass

New in EB real estate: located in the heart of the picturesque Catskill “book village” of Hobart, NY, this well-loved boutique inn & gastropub is ready for its next proprietor. 

Bring a new vision to the many opportunities this property, with features including:

🏠 Main building with five bedrooms and six bathrooms;
🍽️ Restaurant with cozy bar, dining rooms seating up to 55 guests, and a fully-equipped commercial kitchen;
🏡 Outbuildings include a barn with new flooring (perfect for dancing!), picturesque schoolhouse begging to be converted into a tiny guesthouse, and a shed for storage;
🌿 One acre property with creekside beer garden, cantina/bar with outdoor grill for serving drinks and food, bocce court, and fire pits;
🕺🏼 Outdoor stage with new electrical and sound system (suitable for weddings and events);
🛋️ Included in the sale are all restaurant equipment and furniture, catering equipment, glassware, tableware, cutlery, guest room furnishings, draperies, rugs, lines, etc.

This turn-key opportunity is centrally located on Main St in Hobart, NY, a village home to eight independent bookstores, recently profiled by The NY Times. 📚 

Last but not least, for those looking for the ultimate live-work Upstate situation, @UpstateCurious also listed the adjoining property at 794 Main Street: an expansive and charming 4-bedroom home with original details, plus a fully-renovated guesthouse with an additional bedroom, with river frontage. 

More pics and info, link in bio. Asking $1.1m; adjoining property (separate sale) asking $695k. Listed by Danny Romero @agentinthewoods and Hillary Kolos @catskillhillz at @upstatecurious. For showings or inquiries, buyers should contact Hillary Kolos at hillary@upstatecurious.com. 

Photos: 1, 4, 10 by @pbcrosby; 2-3, 5-9 by @philmansfieldphotography.

Weekend inspiration: @modchaletcatskill in East Jewett, NY. ✨ It’s the last call for winter at this cozy home, 15 minutes to the slopes at Windham & Hunter Mountains — or book now in advance of the busy spring & summer season.

Features at this stylish retreat include:

🏠 Three bedrooms, two bathrooms sleeping up to 10 guests;
🌲 Large deck with outdoor seating, grill, gas fire pit and hot tub;
🛁 Primary bathroom with jacuzzi soaking tub;
🔥 Sun-drenched living room with large picture windows & Italian pellet stove for cozy nights by the fire;
🍽️ 100 inch white oak dining table seating 10; 
⚡️ Electric vehicle charger;
🥾 Close proximity to ski slopes in winter & hiking trails for warmer months — see our guide for recommendations!

This modern getaway books far in advance, but still has lots of availability for the upcoming season.

To plan a stay, check Escape Brooklyn’s mini-guide to the area (plus the link to book) at the link in bio. Book direct via the link in @modchaletcatskill bio.

Photos: @escape_brooklyn

New in EB real estate: Magnolia Lake House in Ferndale, NY.

Just 95 miles from New York City, Magnolia Lake House is serenely perched on the shores of Lake Barnabee. This recently renovated home in the foothills of the Catskills is calm, cool and collected. Additionally, the property adjoins a separate parcel with a home for sale, with the option to purchase both.

Offered at $399k, Magnolia Lake House features include:
🏠 Three bedroom, three bathroom home;
🍸 Finished basement with wet bar and exercise room;
🌊 Private lakefront with dock;
💵 Short-term rental friendly;
☀️ Sundeck & screened-in porch;
🏘️ Adjoining carriage house with one bedroom, one bathroom, sundeck and garage.

The Magnolia Lakehouse is flanked by a separate listing, Magnolia Carriage House ($199k), on an adjoining parcel. The two houses are situated on two separate parcels and may be purchased separately or together. See more details about each at the listing, link in bio.

Listed by @troutlily.escapes and @catskillmountainhouses. 

‼️ Open House Sunday, March 5, noon-2pm at 15 Indian Lake Road in Ferndale, NY. Please direct inquiries & RSVP to the open house,  by contacting jill@catskillmountainhouses.com.

Photos: 1, 6, 7, 10 by @pbcrosby. 2-5, 8, 9 by @shelterupstate.

New in EB real estate: a renovated farmhouse & cedar barn in Willow, NY ✨

115 miles from NYC, 7 miles from Woodstock, this turn-key property offers a perfect respite from the city: sit on the front wrap-around porch views of open skies and Mount Tobias, enjoy fireside dining in the open kitchen-dining space, and soak in a claw foot tub after a day of hiking or skiing nearby.

Features include:
🏠 Five bedroom, four bathroom, three story farmhouse;
📐 1,908 total square footage on .63 acres;
⛰️ Wrap-around porch with phenomenal views of Mount Tobias;
🌿 Fenced-in garden;
🔥 Cozy wood stove in dining room for fireside dining;
🛁 Multiple claw-foot soaking tubs;
🐴 Separate cedar barn with storage, partial kitchen and bathroom.

Asking $949k. More pics and info, link in bio.

Listed by Rose Noone @upstate_realtor at Coldwell Banker Village Green. For showings or inquiries contact 845-679-2255, or rosenoone@mac.com.

